00:00:00,030 --> 00:00:06,970
Timing and subtitles brought to you by The Imperial Coroners @ Viki.com

2
00:00:08,030 --> 00:00:11,380
The Prince sent people to save me and found my baggage for me.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,200
I've never seen such a good official like him.

4
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:16,900
It would be great if I can work with him.

5
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,939
The Prince must be the Handsome Judge.

6
00:00:21,939 --> 00:00:25,770
Otherwise, how would he know so much about the Handsome Judge?

7
00:00:33,650 --> 00:00:36,650
Miss, I think you better confess.

8
00:00:36,650 --> 00:00:38,909
You have tasted the food in the jail.

9
00:00:38,910 --> 00:00:40,689
Don't you want a quick death?

10
00:00:40,689 --> 00:00:42,800
A life for a life.

11
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,850
I have nothing to say.

12
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:49,389
I can't report to Commandery Prince An just with your life.

13
00:00:49,389 --> 00:00:50,489
Let's talk about this.

14
00:00:50,489 --> 00:00:54,149
I heard from Commandery Prince An that you killed Yan Ming to steal something.

15
00:00:54,149 --> 00:00:55,459
You are a weak woman.

16
00:00:55,460 --> 00:00:57,839
It's not easy for you to use great effort to steal something.

17
00:00:57,840 --> 00:01:00,909
I'm not asking you to return it.

18
00:01:00,910 --> 00:01:03,359
Just tell me what kind of stuff it is.

19
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,860
I'll give Commandery Prince An a similar one to finish my task.

20
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:09,600
It's a win-win solution.

21
00:01:10,210 --> 00:01:12,899
Vice Minister Jing has a glib tongue indeed.

22
00:01:12,899 --> 00:01:17,280
Since Prince An doesn't know what I stole, you can put him off

23
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:20,680
with anything you want.

24
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,079
Why bother?

25
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:26,110
You really stole something from Yan Ming?

26
00:01:27,310 --> 00:01:29,970
I didn't believe Commandery Prince An when he told me about it.

27
00:01:29,970 --> 00:01:32,060
Yan Ming is a nerd.

28
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:34,149
There are a few valuable paintings and calligraphy works in his manor.

29
00:01:34,150 --> 00:01:37,369
But they are not worth enough to get him killed.

30
00:01:37,369 --> 00:01:40,359
And you had no chance to take the thing out of

31
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,309
Yan Manor on the night when it happened.

32
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:44,679
I thought Commandery Prince An made a mistake.

33
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:48,419
Now it seems that I really have to give him something to finish my task.

34
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:53,270
To be frank,

35
00:01:53,270 --> 00:01:56,750
I really want to put him off with something.

36
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,229
But who is Commandery Prince An?

37
00:01:58,230 --> 00:01:59,680
He is Deity Erlang.
(T/N: Erlang Shen is a Chinese god with a third truth-seeing eye in the middle of his forehead)

38
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:02,439
Somehow he got one more truth-seeing eye than others.

39
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:05,430
It's not as easy as you think to put him off.

40
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:06,999
Let's take a look at you.

41
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,139
You used great effort to cover the blood and hide the weapon.

42
00:02:11,139 --> 00:02:13,570
But he still found you out.

43
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:18,619
I know you hid the thing you stole in Yan Manor.

44
00:02:18,619 --> 00:02:23,329
I need to send the interrogation record to Commandery Prince An tonight.

45
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,109
You are a smart woman.

46
00:02:27,110 --> 00:02:28,079
Think about it.

47
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:30,819
If I hand in the record and Commandery Prince An closes the case,

48
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:32,909
the thing you hid in Yan Manor will be safe.

49
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:34,999
Then you can give it to anyone you want.

50
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:39,030
Just tell me what kind of stuff it is.

51
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:41,220
Can I trust what you say?

52
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:50,700
You really hid the thing in Yan's mansion?

53
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,300
You...!

54
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:59,039
[The Imperial Coroner]

55
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:02,660
[Episode 3]

56
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:09,959
Your Highness, there are all kinds of people in Chang'an.

57
00:03:09,959 --> 00:03:11,479
This girl is so credulous.

58
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:13,359
It's dangerous for her to stay in Chang'an.

59
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,319
Should I warn her a little bit?

60
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,439
After all, safety awareness is necessary.

61
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,239
Her parents can say that.

62
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,569
Her relatives and friends can say that.

63
00:03:20,569 --> 00:03:22,479
Ordinary people can also say that.

64
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:24,089
But officials like us can never say that.

65
00:03:24,089 --> 00:03:26,769
If the official asks people to be on a defensive day and night

66
00:03:26,769 --> 00:03:28,690
and be cautious all the time,

67
00:03:28,690 --> 00:03:30,590
why would the court keep us?

68
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:32,319
Please calm down. I was wrong.

69
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:34,780
Your Highness, Miss Chu has finished the autopsy.

70
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:41,431
- How do you know that?
- What?

71
00:03:41,431 --> 00:03:43,040
The words you just said.

72
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,789
The officials can't say that and why would the court keep you...

73
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:47,099
That's what the Handsome Judge said.

74
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:48,960
How do you know that?

75
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:57,129
Has the Handsome Judge you've been talking about also said that?

76
00:03:57,129 --> 00:03:58,689
Yes, that's what he said.

77
00:03:58,689 --> 00:04:01,239
You have never seen that Handsome Judge,

78
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,960
how do you know what he said?

79
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,159
I heard a lot about him.

80
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:09,029
He said those words when he was admonishing the corrupt officials.

81
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:12,109
Where did you hear about his deeds?

82
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:13,519
I just know it.

83
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,750
You haven't told me how you know these words.

84
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:19,210
I also heard it from someone else.

85
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:22,910
How is the autopsy?

86
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:24,109
I've finished it.

87
00:04:24,110 --> 00:04:25,549
But there is something strange.

88
00:04:25,550 --> 00:04:27,349
Your Higness, can you come with me and check it?

89
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,750
Okay.

90
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:39,540
The dead were male. He was older than 30 years old.

91
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:42,890
The cause of death is being shot by a short arrow in the heart.

92
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:47,169
His legs or feet were fine.

93
00:04:47,169 --> 00:04:48,889
He pretended to have a limp.

94
00:04:48,889 --> 00:04:50,479
I should have found it out at the time.

95
00:04:50,479 --> 00:04:51,879
But I panicked.

96
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,919
It's not your fault.

97
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,099
He wanted to hurt you,

98
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,840
he would attack you no matter if you found it out or not.

99
00:04:57,370 --> 00:04:59,960
Although he pretended to have a limp,

100
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:02,539
he did have many scars on his body.

101
00:05:02,539 --> 00:05:05,039
The oldest one is five or six years old.

102
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,829
The newest one is about one month old.

103
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:08,850
They are all sharp injuries.

104
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:12,240
He should be someone who used swords and spears a lot.

105
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:15,220
There is a thick callus on his right hand's purlicue.

106
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:17,999
Based on the position and the shape of the callus,

107
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,340
he should use knives a lot.

108
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:24,130
But... there is one strange thing.

109
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:26,920
This man used his right hand a lot,

110
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,199
but he was left-handed.

111
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,299
What do you mean by that?

112
00:05:29,299 --> 00:05:30,929
The callus on his right hand means he
[Swordsman]

113
00:05:30,929 --> 00:05:33,449
often held a knife with his right hand.
[Swordsman]

114
00:05:33,449 --> 00:05:35,949
When he hijacked me, he also held the knife with his right hand.

115
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:40,010
But the callus caused by writing is on his left hand,
[Scholar]

116
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:44,639
which means he wrote with his left hand and held a knife with his right hand.

117
00:05:44,639 --> 00:05:47,560
A left-handed scholar
[Swordsman Scholar]

118
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,410
and right-handed swordsman. This person was too weird.

119
00:05:50,410 --> 00:05:53,950
What's the difference between me and the man in charge?

120
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:56,790
A beard.

121
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,540
Isn't it just a beard?

122
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:06,450
Zhou Han greets Eunuch Qin.

123
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:10,970
Have you finished it?

124
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:12,890
It was one step away.

125
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:15,370
Xiao Jinyu's Chief Guardsman, Wu Jiang

126
00:06:15,370 --> 00:06:19,240
suddenly showed up with his men and took that female coroner away.

127
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:25,050
Did you men fight with Xiao Jinyu's people?

128
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:26,249
Yes.

129
00:06:26,249 --> 00:06:29,460
But we've been very careful to conceal our moves.

130
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:31,939
The captive was silenced in time.

131
00:06:31,939 --> 00:06:35,310
What about the body?

132
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,560
Zhou!

133
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:56,780
Can't you clean up your own mess now?

134
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:57,849
Please rest assured.

135
00:06:57,849 --> 00:07:00,449
That person never met anyone from the Judicial Service.

136
00:07:00,449 --> 00:07:02,700
Xiao Jinyu won't know him.

137
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,590
What a fool.

138
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,760
Please calm down, I'm slow witted.

139
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,240
You are not slow witted.

140
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,720
You are retarded.

141
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,409
Let me ask you.

142
00:07:18,409 --> 00:07:23,450
Did your men see the pendant again?

143
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:24,860
Yes.

144
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:27,640
But they didn't get it.

145
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:30,479
Find some clever men and keep a close eye

146
00:07:30,479 --> 00:07:35,910
on Xiao Jinyu and Princess Xiping.

147
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:41,070
Let me know immediately if anything happens.

148
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:43,460
Especially when it's about the pendant.

149
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:55,350
What's more, go back and shave the hair around your mouth.

150
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:59,370
I'll kill everyone in your family

151
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:01,949
if I see one more hair again.

152
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,069
I know.

153
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:04,670
Get out!

154
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:17,600
Master, would Zhou Han, this idiot, implicate us?

155
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:22,220
Keep an eye on the outside.

156
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,810
Yes sir.

157
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:31,059
It wouldn't be strange if he was originally in the army.

158
00:08:31,059 --> 00:08:32,429
In the army?

159
00:08:32,430 --> 00:08:35,349
A martial art master would hold the weapon with his hand

160
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:37,229
that he is comfortable with.

161
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:38,879
But it's different in the army.

162
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,759
The soldier must hold the weapon with the right hand, without exception.

163
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:46,949
Therefore, the left-handed will become ambidextrous after they join the army.

164
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,279
I just arrived in Chang'an.

165
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,219
I haven't offended anyone who served as a soldier.

166
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,909
You didn't offend him.

167
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,199
It's he who has an eye on you.

168
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,080
On me?

169
00:08:57,150 --> 00:09:00,750
I have no money.

170
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,529
- I see.
- What?

171
00:09:02,529 --> 00:09:04,710
When he hijacked me,

172
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:07,029
he told me that he wouldn't kill me if I go with him.

173
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:08,519
I think he fell in love with me.

174
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,360
He wanted to take me back and make me his wife.

175
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,300
It's getting late.

176
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,779
Miss Chu. You...

177
00:09:19,370 --> 00:09:22,549
Chu Chu, have you found a place to stay in Chang'an?

178
00:09:22,549 --> 00:09:24,420
Not yet.

179
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:27,369
I'm worried that the inn owner doesn't want to take in a coroner.

180
00:09:27,369 --> 00:09:29,489
I wanted to find a deserted temple.

181
00:09:29,489 --> 00:09:32,049
But there seems to be no deserted temple here.

182
00:09:32,049 --> 00:09:35,250
The stores will be closed half an hour later.

183
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,229
I've taken too much of your time today.

184
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:40,390
You can stay in the Three Judicial Chief Ministries if you want.

185
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:44,059
It is also convenient for me to discuss these unfinished cases with you at any time.

186
00:09:44,059 --> 00:09:46,650
Live in the Three Judicial Chief Ministries?

187
00:09:46,650 --> 00:09:50,600
I also live in the Three Judicial Chief Ministries.

188
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:54,120
Well, do you have other plans for the night?

189
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,730
No. I'm willing to.

190
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,339
I can work for you if you don't mind.

191
00:09:59,339 --> 00:10:00,789
I can do anything.

192
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:02,539
I won't stay there and eat your food for free.

193
00:10:02,539 --> 00:10:04,960
[Three Judicial Chief Ministries]

194
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,399
Miss Chu, please have some tea.

195
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,529
You are...

196
00:10:16,529 --> 00:10:18,619
I'm a maidservant here, Lian Qiao.

197
00:10:18,619 --> 00:10:21,129
You can order me if you need anything.

198
00:10:21,129 --> 00:10:22,570
No.

199
00:10:22,570 --> 00:10:25,369
- Have you been working here for many years?
- Yes.

200
00:10:25,369 --> 00:10:27,529
You must know a lot about the Prince, right?

201
00:10:27,529 --> 00:10:30,300
What do you want to know?

202
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:37,050
Is the Prince married?

203
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:39,240
The Prince isn't married.

204
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,760
No way.

205
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,639
How is he not married at this age?

206
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:48,279
In our Pingle Town, a man at his age should become a father long ago.

207
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:51,150
The Prince is still young.

208
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:55,839
How is Miss Chu doing?

209
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,249
Miss Chu has settled down.

210
00:10:57,249 --> 00:10:59,299
Our guards live in Liutao Office.

211
00:10:59,299 --> 00:11:01,339
They will report immediately if anything happens.

212
00:11:01,339 --> 00:11:03,749
Did she ask you anything about the manor?

213
00:11:03,749 --> 00:11:04,789
Never.

214
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:07,641
But Miss Chu asked me about a place.

215
00:11:07,641 --> 00:11:10,579
- What place?
- Do you know where the Six Gates is?

216
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:13,640
The Six Gates is the Three Judicial Chief Ministries.

217
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,749
Here?

218
00:11:15,749 --> 00:11:17,209
Not really.

219
00:11:17,209 --> 00:11:20,370
The Six Gates is what the people working in the office call it.

220
00:11:20,370 --> 00:11:22,530
It's a nickname. It's a joke.

221
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:23,619
No.

222
00:11:23,619 --> 00:11:28,059
I'm not talking about this Six Gates, but the Six Gates

223
00:11:28,059 --> 00:11:31,190
with constables and the Handsome Judge.

224
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:33,999
Let her do whatever she wants in the manor

225
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,439
and give her what she wants.

226
00:11:36,439 --> 00:11:39,130
I'd like to see what she's up to.

227
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:41,470
Does he have someone he likes?

228
00:11:42,350 --> 00:11:45,589
Why are you so interested in the Prince's love life?

229
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:47,419
I just don't get it.

230
00:11:47,419 --> 00:11:52,149
What kind of woman can match such a handsome man like the Prince?

231
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:54,740
It would be best if she is

232
00:11:54,740 --> 00:11:57,909
a lady with double-fold eyelids and a high nose.

233
00:11:57,910 --> 00:11:59,989
With the appearance of the Prince,

234
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:03,160
their child will be really good-looking.

235
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:05,789
I dare not discuss the Prince's personal life.

236
00:12:05,789 --> 00:12:09,379
But what you just said, that's how the girls in Chang'an

237
00:12:09,379 --> 00:12:11,189
talk about Vice Minister Jing.

238
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:14,571
It's rare that a girl would praise the Prince the way you do.

239
00:12:14,571 --> 00:12:19,080
The girls in Chang'an do have a strange taste.

240
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:21,710
How handsome the Prince is.

241
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:24,510
By the way, I also want to know

242
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,389
if there is any work I can do for the Prince.

243
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:28,210
Anything will do.

244
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:29,980
Work?

245
00:12:33,710 --> 00:12:37,129
Miss Chu asked me to bring you a hot boiled egg.

246
00:12:37,129 --> 00:12:38,530
I'm not hungry.

247
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:40,509
She asked me to peel the egg

248
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:42,589
and roll it on the wound on your forehead.

249
00:12:42,589 --> 00:12:44,869
It can promote blood circulation and disperse blood stasis.

250
00:12:44,869 --> 00:12:46,570
Go ahead.

251
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:48,569
Your Highness.

252
00:12:48,569 --> 00:12:51,719
You've been suspecting Miss Chu's background,

253
00:12:51,719 --> 00:12:54,319
but why did you still ask her to do autopsies again and again?

254
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:57,140
Although she is suspicious,

255
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:59,240
she is a talented coroner

256
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,650
indeed.

257
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:05,470
She is more gifted than other coroners.

258
00:13:05,470 --> 00:13:08,329
It's not something you can have through learning.

259
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:11,789
I've heard that those who play zithers or draw need to be gifted.

260
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,199
A coroner's work is to find out how a person dies.

261
00:13:14,199 --> 00:13:17,180
Does it make any difference being gifted or not?

262
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:21,280
For ordinary coroners, a corpse is just a corpse.

263
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:26,430
But, for her, these corpses seem to be alive.

264
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,020
Alive?

265
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,709
She can feel what they feel and think what they think.

266
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:35,689
I have never seen such a peculiar coroner like her.

267
00:13:35,689 --> 00:13:37,890
It would be the best

268
00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:41,330
if my suspicion of her is just misunderstanding.

269
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:44,839
If not, I would like to give her a chance

270
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,419
to get back on the right track.

271
00:13:46,419 --> 00:13:47,809
I believe that.

272
00:13:47,809 --> 00:13:49,609
Jing Yi was going down the wrong path at that time,

273
00:13:49,609 --> 00:13:52,490
but you still pulled him back to the right track.

274
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,880
What?

275
00:14:15,610 --> 00:14:16,789
What do you mean?

276
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,830
Are you asking me to roll away?

277
00:14:18,830 --> 00:14:20,869
Well, I've worked my butt off.

278
00:14:20,870 --> 00:14:22,649
It's under curfew now and I can't go home.

279
00:14:22,649 --> 00:14:24,989
I just got here, and you did that to me. Just go.

280
00:14:25,001 --> 00:14:28,200
There are snacks from Princess Xiping's Manor.

281
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:37,100
It's the top grade.

282
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:38,829
What about the confession?

283
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:41,600
It's kind of troublesome now.

284
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:46,469
The scroll you talked about is really hidden in the Yan manor.

285
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:48,550
I have found it.

286
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,749
But when I took the scroll back to the Court of Judicial Review

287
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:57,590
and wanted to question that dancing girl, she died of poison.

288
00:14:57,590 --> 00:15:00,729
I have found someone to check her body. It's aconitine.
(T/N: Aconitine poisoning is related to the rapid onset of life-threatening heart rhythm changes.)

289
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,810
Aconitine?

290
00:15:04,810 --> 00:15:06,289
She is a dancing girl.

291
00:15:06,289 --> 00:15:08,039
How did she get this highly poisonous herb?

292
00:15:08,039 --> 00:15:10,800
She might get it while dancing at some place.

293
00:15:12,490 --> 00:15:14,330
This is the scroll.

294
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:21,010
This is a book about anecdotes of the Wuzong Dynasty.

295
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:24,339
Yan Ming wrote a bunch of messy comments next to it.
[Duke Chang The Imperial Family]

296
00:15:24,339 --> 00:15:27,099
He seemed to be interested in
[Mystery]

297
00:15:27,099 --> 00:15:28,299
the Emperor Wuzong's young son, Duke Chang.

298
00:15:28,299 --> 00:15:29,879
I mean, Yan Ming was a scholar.

299
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,390
He didn't study poems and songs,

300
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:35,199
but study dead people like coroners.

301
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,710
Yan Ming... might be looking for someone.

302
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:40,390
Looking for someone?

303
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,639
Who was Yan Ming looking for?

304
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,050
A dead person.

305
00:15:45,050 --> 00:15:47,960
A person that no one can find.

306
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:51,069
What are you talking about?  I think Yan Ming had nothing better to do.

307
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,759
Anyway, the murderer who killed Yan Ming is already dead.

308
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:57,399
We can offer an explanation to the Emperor now.

309
00:15:57,399 --> 00:16:00,030
Watch your attitude when you go to court tomorrow.

310
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:03,609
My father and Mr. Xue told you many times

311
00:16:03,609 --> 00:16:06,609
to make more friends and less enemies.

312
00:16:06,609 --> 00:16:08,539
I have no intention of making enemies.

313
00:16:08,539 --> 00:16:09,669
That's good.

314
00:16:09,669 --> 00:16:14,660
But those who are against truth and justice are my enemies.

315
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,960
Wash your hands that just touched the poison.

316
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,969
I asked the kitchen to save some food for you.

317
00:16:25,969 --> 00:16:27,469
You rest here tonight.

318
00:16:27,470 --> 00:16:30,249
Tomorrow morning, go to the Shen Army and ask about

319
00:16:30,249 --> 00:16:32,109
if there is a junior officer in his thirties missing

320
00:16:32,110 --> 00:16:35,089
who has been in the army for about five years.

321
00:16:35,089 --> 00:16:36,590
Shen Army?

322
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:38,940
Did those eunuchs cause any trouble again?

323
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:42,989
When we left Yan Manor today, there were soldiers in disguise

324
00:16:42,990 --> 00:16:45,010
who tried to hijack Miss Chu.

325
00:16:45,010 --> 00:16:47,140
They failed

326
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:50,770
and used this to kill the captive.

327
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:54,269
This arrowhead is not something that an ordinary blacksmith can make.

328
00:16:54,269 --> 00:16:58,099
This is made by the Crossbow Agency of the Weapon Bureau

329
00:16:58,099 --> 00:17:00,940
exclusively for the army in the capital.

330
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:05,060
I asked someone to get it from the Crossbow Agency.

331
00:17:09,481 --> 00:17:11,659
Are you suspecting that someone from the Shen Army tried to hijack Chu Chu?

332
00:17:11,659 --> 00:17:12,799
If you verify it

333
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:15,279
and there is such a person missing in the Shen Army,

334
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,640
then it's not a suspicion anymore.

335
00:17:26,930 --> 00:17:29,019
Qian Printing made copper coins illicitly.

336
00:17:29,019 --> 00:17:30,159
The dancing girl.

337
00:17:30,159 --> 00:17:31,919
The aconitine.
[Qia]

338
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:34,140
They are all related to the Southwest.

339
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:40,580
Why does Prince An care so much about

340
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:42,680
the witch doctor's pendant?

341
00:17:45,020 --> 00:17:48,119
Yan Ming was killed for looking into the son of the late emperor.

342
00:17:48,119 --> 00:17:51,860
The dancer who killed him took poison when she was found out.

343
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:54,029
Prince An said he is not the Handsome Judge.

344
00:17:54,029 --> 00:17:57,000
But why does he know so much about the Handsome Judge?

345
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,130
The case of Yan Ming is not that simple.

346
00:18:13,450 --> 00:18:15,520
Help!

347
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,159
Something bad happened!

348
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,920
Help!

349
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:26,409
Madam. Madam, are you okay?

350
00:18:26,409 --> 00:18:27,910
What happened?

351
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:31,060
Master... Master...

352
00:18:31,060 --> 00:18:33,410
Master died.

353
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,380
Madam.

354
00:18:44,361 --> 00:18:45,630
It's okay, Madam. It wasn't me

355
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:46,750
Really wasn't me!

356
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,800
- It's not me.
- Madam, don't be afraid.

357
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,270
Go get Madam!

358
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:01,280
[Pull out the net and guard the back]
[The Book of Songs]

359
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,380
Master.

360
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:08,000
Master, wake up!

361
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,520
Anybody, get in here.

362
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:27,159
- Your Highness.
- What happened?

363
00:19:27,159 --> 00:19:29,139
Have all the chickens of Chang'an flown here to file a complaint?

364
00:19:29,139 --> 00:19:30,339
The chickens didn't fly here. Miss Chu bought them.

365
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:32,039
Miss Chu bought them.

366
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:34,320
Why would she buy chickens?

367
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:35,689
- Your Highness.
- Go ahead.

368
00:19:35,689 --> 00:19:37,829
There is the obituary from Minister Feng's Manor.

369
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:39,430
Obituary?

370
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:44,730
[Feng Manor Liu]

371
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:46,349
Feng Jie passed away last night.

372
00:19:46,350 --> 00:19:48,499
Didn't Minister Feng go to the Southwest to inspect military affairs?

373
00:19:48,499 --> 00:19:50,160
How did he die?

374
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:52,689
Tell the housekeeper that I'll go to the Palace first.

375
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:54,069
I'll go to Feng's Manor to express condolences after I come back.

376
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:55,039
Yes.

377
00:19:55,039 --> 00:19:57,460
[Three Judicial Chief Ministries]

378
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,320
You are back, Your Highness.

379
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,400
Your Highness.

380
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,561
You may rise.

381
00:20:13,561 --> 00:20:16,000
- You are...
- Raise chickens.

382
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,399
I made a coop last night.

383
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,570
I asked Lian Qiao to buy these chickens this morning.

384
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,940
I bought them with the wages you gave me.

385
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:24,999
The chicken in Chang'an is too expensive.

386
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,570
If it's in our Pingle Town,

387
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:30,330
I can at least buy dozens of chickens with this money.

388
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:32,039
Didn't Wu Jiang tell you

389
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,690
that you don't need to worry about the food here?

390
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:36,399
General Wu did.

391
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:41,040
But I can't live here for free.

392
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,461
Lian Qiao said that there are people

393
00:20:42,461 --> 00:20:45,900
who wash clothes and cook for you.

394
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,799
You don't need me to do it. I asked them.

395
00:20:47,799 --> 00:20:50,090
You didn't raise chickens or grow food here.

396
00:20:50,090 --> 00:20:52,060
There happens to be a vacant plot of land here.

397
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:54,030
So I made use of it for you.

398
00:20:54,030 --> 00:20:57,750
After these chickens grow up, they can lay eggs when it gets warmer.

399
00:20:57,750 --> 00:20:59,999
Chickens lay eggs, and there will be more chickens.

400
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,760
Considering the price of the commodity in Chang'an,

401
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,360
I can make a lot of money for you.

402
00:21:05,830 --> 00:21:07,890
- Thank you for all the trouble.
- Not at all.

403
00:21:07,890 --> 00:21:10,810
After the winter is over, I will clean up the ground in the backyard

404
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,469
and grow vegetables and grains.

405
00:21:12,470 --> 00:21:13,949
Are you going to grow vegetables here?

406
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:17,290
It's a waste to only raise chickens in such a big area.

407
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:20,260
But I don't know what should be grown here.

408
00:21:20,260 --> 00:21:23,919
If it's in our Pingle Town, the rice in the backyard

409
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:27,490
is enough to feed the big family for a year.

410
00:21:29,450 --> 00:21:32,289
Lian Qiao. Go to prepare a set of maid's dress.

411
00:21:32,289 --> 00:21:34,110
Yes sir.

412
00:21:35,430 --> 00:21:39,540
Miss Chu, let's talk about these stuffs later.

413
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:42,919
I don't know if you can do one favor for me.

414
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:44,229
Autopsies?

415
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:45,210
Yes.

416
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:47,360
Of course I can.

417
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:50,279
But it's not for the offices.

418
00:21:50,279 --> 00:21:51,700
It's my personal affairs.

419
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,030
Don't worry.

420
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:57,690
Whether it's for you or the offices, I will do the autopsy well.

421
00:21:57,690 --> 00:21:59,150
I won't put you off.

422
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:02,530
This time you can't do it in public, and you can't use any tools.

423
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:06,430
You also need to dress up as my maid and come with me.

424
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:07,740
Is it okay?

425
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:11,970
Dress up as a maid and do the autopsy?

426
00:22:11,970 --> 00:22:15,580
But I've never done that before.

427
00:22:15,580 --> 00:22:18,600
If you think I can do it, I'll go with you.

428
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,829
You can do it.

429
00:22:19,830 --> 00:22:23,490
Feed these grains to the chickens.

430
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:40,880
Thank you.

431
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,130
This dress is too troublesome.

432
00:22:43,130 --> 00:22:45,519
Putting it on is even harder than making a basket.

433
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:47,700
You will get used to it.

434
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:08,329
Your Highness. Don't be afraid.

435
00:23:08,329 --> 00:23:09,910
They don't bite people.

436
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,920
How would I be afraid of them?

437
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:14,380
I just don't want to stain my garments.

438
00:23:15,010 --> 00:23:19,609
Your Highness, it's the first time for me wearing this kind of clothes.

439
00:23:19,609 --> 00:23:23,250
How should I work dressed like this?

440
00:23:24,690 --> 00:23:28,080
Stay here for a while, I'll teach you later.

441
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:40,521
- The towel.
- Isn't the towel right in front of you?

442
00:23:40,521 --> 00:23:44,510
You are a maid. If I take it by myself, why would I need you?

443
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,940
Use your both hands.

444
00:23:51,210 --> 00:23:52,910
Keep your head down.

445
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:56,390
It's too much, lift up a little bit.

446
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:02,730
Your Highness, my third neck bone is about to break.

447
00:24:04,850 --> 00:24:06,650
Stand up.

448
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:07,780
Keep your spine straight.

449
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:10,469
Place the towel on the palms of your hands.

450
00:24:10,470 --> 00:24:11,930
Lower your elbows.

451
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:14,309
Raise your wrist bones to the collarbones.

452
00:24:14,310 --> 00:24:15,799
Keep your sixth and seventh neck bones straight.

453
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:18,120
Bend the fifth to the first neck bones.

454
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:20,120
Withdraw your jawbone a little bit.

455
00:24:22,140 --> 00:24:23,920
Have I allowed you to move?

456
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,330
Have you remembered this posture?

457
00:24:25,330 --> 00:24:28,660
Yes. I've remembered the position of each bone.

458
00:24:28,660 --> 00:24:30,440
Put it back.

459
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:33,890
Answer yes.

460
00:24:33,890 --> 00:24:35,650
Yes.

461
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:38,050
Keep your hands folded.

462
00:24:38,050 --> 00:24:39,109
Put your right leg back.

463
00:24:39,110 --> 00:24:41,010
Then squat down.

464
00:25:00,530 --> 00:25:03,000
Okay, get up.

465
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:21,800
How dare you!

466
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,280
You...

467
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,999
Why do you have no scars?

468
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,400
Weren't you hurt before?

469
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,210
- What?
- A sword wound.

470
00:25:29,210 --> 00:25:31,810
About two inches long, so deep that the bone was visible.

471
00:25:31,810 --> 00:25:33,899
After healing, there is a scar as thin as an ink line.

472
00:25:33,899 --> 00:25:35,700
No.

473
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:38,770
Is he really not the Handsome Judge?

474
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:40,440
What did you say?

475
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:42,870
Nothing.

476
00:25:42,870 --> 00:25:45,930
But you are really white.

477
00:25:45,930 --> 00:25:51,600
The creamy skin in the book should be like this.

478
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:54,240
Enough, come with me.

479
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,700
[Feng Manor]
[Funeral]

480
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:01,529
Banxia greets Your Highness.

481
00:26:01,529 --> 00:26:03,430
You are exempted.

482
00:26:03,430 --> 00:26:06,069
Is Aunt Banxia here to mourn for your mother?

483
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:07,250
Yes.

484
00:26:07,250 --> 00:26:10,010
- You are...
- I'm also here to mourn Minister Feng.

485
00:26:10,010 --> 00:26:12,760
I'll leave then.

486
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:19,709
Your Highness. Did I just give it away?

487
00:26:19,709 --> 00:26:20,690
Yes.

488
00:26:20,690 --> 00:26:22,960
- What to do then?
- It doesn't matter.

489
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,399
It's okay that you gave it away here.

490
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:27,690
Just follow my instructions after we get in there.

491
00:26:27,690 --> 00:26:29,070
- Senior Jing.
- Okay.

492
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:32,440
Scholar Xue and Vice Minister Jing have arrived!

493
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,220
Senior Jing.

494
00:26:34,220 --> 00:26:36,010
Sir.

495
00:26:40,370 --> 00:26:43,020
After we get to Feng Manor, I will go to the mourning hall.

496
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:46,450
After I finish the funeral service, I will give the incense to you.

497
00:26:46,450 --> 00:26:48,559
Then you take a look at Feng Jie's body

498
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:50,039
when you insert the incense into the burner.

499
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,480
I can only take one look?

500
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:55,949
If you can tell the cause of his death by taking one look, then yes.

501
00:26:55,950 --> 00:26:58,110
What if I can't?

502
00:27:11,110 --> 00:27:13,950
Miss. Let me do it.

503
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,571
Hurry up.

504
00:27:41,571 --> 00:27:43,519
Servants! Servants!

505
00:27:43,519 --> 00:27:44,890
Clear it up.

506
00:27:44,890 --> 00:27:46,720
Come on, get up.

507
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:48,009
Come on. My lords.

508
00:27:48,009 --> 00:27:50,490
Please move to the side hall to rest.

509
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,420
These are... scratches?

510
00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:54,651
Miss! Madam, look at her!

511
00:27:54,651 --> 00:27:56,200
What are you doing?

512
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,159
These incense ashes were splashed on Minister Feng.

513
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:00,370
He can't wear this shroud.

514
00:28:00,370 --> 00:28:01,730
What are you doing?

515
00:28:01,730 --> 00:28:04,150
When ashes fall on the shroud, it's the dead soul protesting against injustice.

516
00:28:04,150 --> 00:28:04,960
It's unlucky. You should change the shroud now.

517
00:28:04,960 --> 00:28:06,189
You should change the shroud now.

518
00:28:06,190 --> 00:28:07,189
What injustice? What nonsense are you talking about?

519
00:28:08,489 --> 00:28:09,910
Don't slander our Master. Well...

520
00:28:09,910 --> 00:28:12,110
Don't talk nonsense. Apologize to Madam Feng now.

521
00:28:12,110 --> 00:28:13,250
I'm not talking nonsense.

522
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:15,250
Don't you talk back!

523
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,639
Your Highness, she is not talking nonsense.

524
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:19,510
I have also heard about it before.

525
00:28:19,510 --> 00:28:22,490
Madam, I think you better change Minister Feng's shroud.

526
00:28:22,490 --> 00:28:23,510
We don't believe it.

527
00:28:23,510 --> 00:28:26,039
But if someone who believes it sees it and spreads it out,

528
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,589
won't it hurt Minister Feng's reputation?

529
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:29,419
Well...

530
00:28:29,420 --> 00:28:31,740
[Antique Store]

531
00:28:41,270 --> 00:28:45,179
Sir. We got new products from the Southwest.

532
00:28:45,180 --> 00:28:47,030
[Book of Songs]

533
00:28:47,030 --> 00:28:48,330
Give it to me.

534
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:51,690
By the way, Senior Jing rushed us a few times.

535
00:28:51,690 --> 00:28:55,560
Pack his goods according to the list as soon as possible and send them to him.
[Book of Songs]

536
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:56,699
Yes.

537
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:57,759
[illuminate Auspicious]

538
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:59,469
Master passed away suddenly.

539
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:00,890
Everything is prepared in a rush.

540
00:29:00,890 --> 00:29:03,800
Please forgive us if we didn't serve you well.

541
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:06,410
When did Minister Feng return to the capital?

542
00:29:06,410 --> 00:29:10,720
What kind of disease caused his sudden death?

543
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:17,390
Just before the gate closed yesterday, Master entered the capital

544
00:29:17,390 --> 00:29:20,850
and went to the welcome banquet held by his colleagues.

545
00:29:20,850 --> 00:29:23,709
It was a laborious trip and he had a few more drinks

546
00:29:23,710 --> 00:29:26,210
which brought about the terrible disease.

547
00:29:29,490 --> 00:29:33,390
When you get old, you can't neglect your health.

548
00:29:33,390 --> 00:29:35,279
Scholar Xue is right.

549
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:38,010
That's how our Madam said to Master.

550
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:40,110
But Master was busy with official duties

551
00:29:40,110 --> 00:29:43,130
and he turned a deaf ear to her words.

552
00:29:43,130 --> 00:29:46,560
I remember that Minister Feng had no sons but three daughters.

553
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,010
Why didn't I see any of them?

554
00:29:49,010 --> 00:29:51,500
Their husbands are talking offices outside the capital.

555
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:54,580
The three ladies are out there with their husbands.

556
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:55,830
Master passed away suddenly.

557
00:29:55,830 --> 00:29:59,290
I'm afraid they won't come back until the day when Master is buried.

558
00:29:59,290 --> 00:30:01,370
What about the Second Lady?

559
00:30:03,090 --> 00:30:05,970
Master went to the Southwest for inspections and had been away for long,

560
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:08,150
he died suddenly just as he came back.

561
00:30:08,150 --> 00:30:10,850
The Second Madam is too sad and she falls sick.

562
00:30:10,850 --> 00:30:12,519
She can't greet guests now.

563
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,030
What's gone is gone. You should comfort her.

564
00:30:15,030 --> 00:30:16,399
Yes.

565
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,580
I'll leave.

566
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:33,789
Princess. I met Prince An before I left Feng Manor.

567
00:30:33,789 --> 00:30:35,799
Jinyu went to Feng Manor to express condolences?

568
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:36,550
Yes.

569
00:30:36,551 --> 00:30:38,309
Did he go there alone?

570
00:30:38,310 --> 00:30:40,039
He also brought a girl.

571
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:42,759
I've asked someone and she is a coroner.

572
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:47,320
Jinyu brought a coroner to Feng Manor to express condolences?

573
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:49,949
Go to the Three Judicial Chief Ministries and tell Jinyu

574
00:30:49,950 --> 00:30:52,349
that there is something really important.

575
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:55,809
- If he doesn't come to me, I'll go to see him.
- Yes.

576
00:30:55,809 --> 00:30:59,900
[Feng Manor]
[Funeral]

577
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:04,930
Good day, Commandery Prince An, Scholar Xue.

578
00:31:04,930 --> 00:31:07,559
What was that about in the mourning hall?

579
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:10,639
I have some doubts. I want to know the truth.

580
00:31:10,639 --> 00:31:12,430
Is there anything wrong?

581
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:14,759
I haven't found it out.

582
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,559
You are getting crazier.

583
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:19,590
What if the Emperor knows it?

584
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,950
Good day, sir.

585
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:32,110
Good day, Senior Jing, Vice Minister Jing.

586
00:31:38,190 --> 00:31:42,709
If you have time, come to my mansion and have a simple meal.

587
00:31:42,710 --> 00:31:45,499
Father, forget it. If Commandery Prince An comes to our manor,

588
00:31:45,499 --> 00:31:47,900
Mother will introduce girls to him again.

589
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:49,189
Just give me a break.

590
00:31:49,190 --> 00:31:51,069
What does it have to do with you

591
00:31:51,070 --> 00:31:52,909
- that your mother introduces girls to Commandery Prince An?
- What does it have to do with me?

592
00:31:52,909 --> 00:31:57,770
The city gate is on fire, disaster is brought to the fish in the moat.

593
00:31:57,770 --> 00:32:00,830
Well... Senior Jing. there have been many trivial matters in the Three Judicial Chief Ministries.

594
00:32:00,830 --> 00:32:03,159
I won't bother you today.

595
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,490
I'll visit Aunt in person some other day.

596
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:08,589
But I have some official affairs to discuss with Jing Yi.

597
00:32:08,590 --> 00:32:11,400
Can you let Jing Yi go back with me?

598
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:12,970
Okay.

599
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:16,039
Be serious about your work with Commandery Prince An.

600
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:18,760
Otherwise, I'll go back and tell your mother about it.

601
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:22,010
Senior Jing, don't worry.

602
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,520
I'll leave.

603
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:28,640
What a tattletale.

604
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:33,950
At lease you parents are healthy.

605
00:32:37,020 --> 00:32:41,260
[Feng Manor]

606
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:44,109
Your Highness, I was really scared.

607
00:32:44,110 --> 00:32:45,639
I thought I was going to give myself away.

608
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:48,430
You really went there to do an autopsy?

609
00:32:49,190 --> 00:32:50,589
Don't you know that?

610
00:32:50,590 --> 00:32:53,040
Then why did you help me out?

611
00:32:53,830 --> 00:32:57,159
Commandery Prince An doesn't attend any wedding or funeral.

612
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,650
He brought a coroner to the funeral this time.

613
00:32:58,650 --> 00:33:00,230
Isn't it obvious?

614
00:33:00,230 --> 00:33:02,970
When the fox preaches, take care of your geese.
(T/N: Proverb that says to be aware about hidden agenda)

615
00:33:04,420 --> 00:33:06,290
Fox?

616
00:33:06,290 --> 00:33:09,640
It's just an inappropriate analogy.

617
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:15,890
Chu Chu, did you find anything from that quick glance?

618
00:33:15,890 --> 00:33:17,610
There is...

619
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:20,800
Hold on. It's time for lunch.

620
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:22,309
Chu Chu, are you hungry?

621
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:24,410
I'm a little hungry.

622
00:33:24,410 --> 00:33:28,640
I fed the chickens but forgot to feed myself this morning.

623
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:32,759
Your Highness, considering how hard we tried to help you.

624
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:35,970
Shouldn't you treat us to a good meal?

625
00:33:35,970 --> 00:33:38,109
No, I'm fine. I am healthy.

626
00:33:38,109 --> 00:33:39,559
It's okay to be hungry for a while.

627
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,879
No way.

628
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:42,999
Your brain can't work well when you are hungry

629
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,719
and it's easy to forget stuffs. And it's easy to make mistakes when you think.

630
00:33:45,719 --> 00:33:49,219
You are a coroner. Shouldn't you know better than I do?

631
00:33:49,219 --> 00:33:52,630
Okay, let's talk while eating.

632
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:54,290
What do you want to eat?

633
00:34:04,220 --> 00:34:06,300
[Rugui Tavern]

634
00:34:06,300 --> 00:34:09,150
Vice Minister Jing, please come in.

635
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:12,050
This is...

636
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:14,950
This is Commandery Prince An from the Three Judicial Chief Ministries.

637
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:17,759
I'm Xu Rugui, the owner of Rugui Tavern.

638
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,710
- Greetings to Commandery Prince An.
- You may rise.

639
00:34:19,710 --> 00:34:20,560
Thank you, Your Highness.

640
00:34:20,561 --> 00:34:21,429
[Rugui Tavern]

641
00:34:21,430 --> 00:34:22,559
The same old dishes.

642
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:24,359
Braised pigeon with soy sauce, seared salamander,

643
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,410
and roast lamb ribs.

644
00:34:26,410 --> 00:34:28,170
Remember, it must be baby lamb.

645
00:34:28,170 --> 00:34:29,820
Don't roast it for too long.

646
00:34:29,820 --> 00:34:33,689
Get us more dipping sauce. I like you nomads' dipping sauce the most.

647
00:34:33,689 --> 00:34:35,559
Rest assured. I got it.

648
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,279
Commandery Prince An, it's your first time to be here,

649
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:41,090
may I introduce you our specialties?

650
00:34:41,090 --> 00:34:42,370
No need.

651
00:34:42,370 --> 00:34:46,519
I want a flower chicken, a sour fish soup and a houttuynia salad.

652
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:49,560
Why did Prince An order Qianzhou dishes?

653
00:34:53,910 --> 00:34:55,909
Your Highness, you do know what to eat.

654
00:34:55,910 --> 00:34:58,030
Houttuynia is rare in Chang'an.

655
00:34:58,030 --> 00:34:59,799
Only Rugui Tavern has it.

656
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:01,359
These three dishes ordered by Commandery Prince An

657
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,999
are all authentic Qianzhou cuisine.

658
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:06,189
There happens to be a cook from Qianzhou.

659
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:08,070
I won't say that the cooking is superb,

660
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:11,709
but this cook can make the authentic Qianzhou taste.

661
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:14,120
Commandery Prince An, Vice Minister Jing. Please wait for a while.

662
00:35:14,120 --> 00:35:16,079
The dishes will be ready soon.

663
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,920
Wait!

664
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:20,910
Get this girl a cup of tea.

665
00:35:23,150 --> 00:35:25,669
Forgive me for being clumsy and neglecting this girl.

666
00:35:25,670 --> 00:35:26,699
It's okay.

667
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:28,000
Sit down.

668
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:36,900
This man looks strange.

669
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:39,740
I'll leave.

670
00:35:42,950 --> 00:35:44,180
Are you a regular here?

671
00:35:44,180 --> 00:35:45,909
Not really.

672
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:48,429
The food is delicious here. But it's too expensive for me.

673
00:35:48,429 --> 00:35:52,190
I won't eat here if no one gives me a treat.

674
00:35:53,090 --> 00:35:56,010
Have you known Feng Jie's death?
[Jiangshan Hall]

675
00:35:56,630 --> 00:36:00,810
Your Majesty. I received an obituary from Feng Manor early in the morning.

676
00:36:00,810 --> 00:36:02,840
I went to Feng Manor to offer my condolences.

677
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:06,429
Minister Feng passed away just after he came back.

678
00:36:06,430 --> 00:36:08,999
The Feng Manor wasn't prepared at all.

679
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,149
It was hectic when I went there.

680
00:36:11,150 --> 00:36:14,279
I feel really sorry for them.

681
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:18,660
The Feng Manor wasn't prepared, wasn't I caught off guard?

682
00:36:18,660 --> 00:36:22,120
Now Feng Jie is gone, someone needs to take over the Ministry of War.

683
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,510
You are right, Your Majesty.

684
00:36:23,510 --> 00:36:24,980
It's easy to talk.

685
00:36:24,980 --> 00:36:27,119
Who can take it over?

686
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,669
Since I took the throne,

687
00:36:28,670 --> 00:36:31,070
I've been racking my brains for my country day and night.

688
00:36:31,070 --> 00:36:35,230
Everyone in court is trying to consolidate the power of Great Tang

689
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:36,820
and restore the prosperity.

690
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:39,730
How important it is to find a talent.

691
00:36:41,470 --> 00:36:46,229
Do you think it's that easy to appoint a third-rank minister?

692
00:36:46,230 --> 00:36:47,800
Feng Jie is only in his early fifties.

693
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:50,570
He is even healthier than those military officers.

694
00:36:50,570 --> 00:36:52,850
How did he die in such a sudden?

695
00:36:52,850 --> 00:36:58,849
I heard from Feng's housekeeper that it was a laborious trip to the southwest

696
00:36:58,849 --> 00:37:01,319
and he had a few more drinks at the welcome banquet,

697
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:05,660
which aroused the terrible disease, leading to his sudden death.

698
00:37:06,430 --> 00:37:09,740
What? He died of drinking?

699
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:20,079
- Prince An, Vice Minister Jing.
- Please enjoy yourselves.

700
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:21,640
Miss, please enjoy yourselves.

701
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:24,840
Feel free to tell me if you need anything else.

702
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:26,770
I'll leave.

703
00:37:30,190 --> 00:37:32,769
Well? These dishes don't suit your appetite?

704
00:37:32,769 --> 00:37:36,679
No. I just feel that this owner looks...

705
00:37:39,230 --> 00:37:40,770
It's nothing.

706
00:37:42,150 --> 00:37:44,130
It has been a hard day for you.

707
00:37:44,130 --> 00:37:45,830
Go ahead and eat.

708
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:52,219
Your Highness. Do you also like Qianzhou food?

709
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:54,189
I never tasted it before.

710
00:37:54,190 --> 00:37:56,279
My older brother is a general stationed in the Southwest.

711
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:58,839
He mentioned these Qianzhou dishes before.

712
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,869
Qianzhou is a thousand miles away from Chang'an.

713
00:38:00,870 --> 00:38:02,389
You have left home at least for one month.

714
00:38:02,390 --> 00:38:05,130
You haven't had your hometown food for some time, right?

715
00:38:05,130 --> 00:38:07,880
You ordered these dishes for me?

716
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:11,899
I treat you two to a meal, of course, I should order dishes for you two.

717
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:18,330
But, Your Highness,

718
00:38:18,330 --> 00:38:20,500
I haven't found the cause of his death.

719
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:21,869
It doesn't matter.

720
00:38:21,870 --> 00:38:24,060
Fill your stomach first.

721
00:38:24,060 --> 00:38:26,220
Come on, give me the bowl.

722
00:38:41,600 --> 00:38:43,500
Thank you, Your Highness.

723
00:38:45,390 --> 00:38:47,090
Thank you, Your Highness.

724
00:38:57,710 --> 00:39:00,720
It should be true that she was born in Qianzhou.

725
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:05,349
Chu Chu, are these Qianzhou dishes authentic?

726
00:39:05,350 --> 00:39:06,669
Yeah, they are really authentic.

727
00:39:06,670 --> 00:39:07,980
I'm glad you enjoy them.

728
00:39:07,980 --> 00:39:09,710
Take your time. Don't feel restrained.

729
00:39:09,710 --> 00:39:11,290
Thank you, Your highness.

730
00:39:11,290 --> 00:39:14,909
Did you find anything in the mourning hall of the Feng Manor?

731
00:39:14,910 --> 00:39:17,319
There are several obvious injuries on Feng Jie's chest.

732
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:20,220
But those are not to hurt him. But to save him.

733
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:23,120
Save him? How to save him?

734
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:24,619
Can I show it to you in person?

735
00:39:24,620 --> 00:39:27,660
You pretend to be Feng Jie. I'll be the one to save him.

736
00:39:27,660 --> 00:39:29,040
Okay.

737
00:39:38,610 --> 00:39:40,450
- What are you doing?
- I'm showing it to you.

738
00:39:40,450 --> 00:39:42,119
Minister Feng should be dead now.

739
00:39:42,120 --> 00:39:44,619
You need to relax and lie down with your eyes closed.

740
00:39:44,620 --> 00:39:47,301
You can't move no matter what I do to you.

741
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:57,430
That should be how Minister Feng got those scratches.

